        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>36 Great Marlborough St</placeName>
                    <date>September 22<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> 1838</date>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I have the honour to transmit, as on former occasions, for the approval of the Lords Commissioner’s of Her Majesty’s Treasury the account of M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> Smith &amp; Elder for the second number of the second part of the “Zoology of the Voyage of the Beagle”, which is now published.<ref target="#foot.f1"/> I beg leave to state, that as before I have examined the account and superintended the expenditure of each part.—</p>
<p>I have the honour to remain | Sir | Your obedient servant | Charles Darwin <lb resp="#mjhawkins"/> To | A. Y. Spearman Esq<hi rend="superscript">r</hi></p>
<p>Treasury Chambers</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Preserved with this letter is an account from <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4407.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Smith, Elder &amp; Co</ref>., dated 1 September 1838, detailing the various costs of <hi rend="italic">Mammalia,</hi> No. 2. The total expense was £47 16<hi rend="italic">s.</hi> 6<hi rend="italic">d.</hi></note>
        </div>        
            
